1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Now it is time to create your My Action Plan — your MAP.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:12,399
This is a tool you will use in every guide throughout the series, and it travels with you.

3
00:00:12,399 --> 00:00:14,399
Your MAP has three sections.

4
00:00:14,399 --> 00:00:18,000
Stop: What is one thing you will stop doing?

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,600
Maybe it is assuming you know what someone needs.

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:26,800
Maybe it is walking past a barrier you have noticed but never reported.

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:30,399
Start: What is one thing you will start doing?

8
00:00:30,399 --> 00:00:35,199
Maybe it is asking every patient how they prefer to receive information.

9
00:00:35,199 --> 00:00:38,399
Maybe it is doing a workspace accessibility scan.

10
00:00:38,399 --> 00:00:44,799
Continue: What is one thing you are already doing well that you want to keep doing?

11
00:00:44,799 --> 00:00:49,199
Maybe you already speak directly to patients rather than their companions.

12
00:00:49,199 --> 00:00:52,799
Maybe you already use plain language in your communications.

13
00:00:52,799 --> 00:00:55,199
Fill in your MAP on screen.

14
00:00:55,199 --> 00:01:00,399
You can also download it as a PDF to keep at your workstation.

15
00:01:00,399 --> 00:01:05,200
Your MAP entries are saved to your learner profile and are private.
